	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jun 25th 3:39 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=32884><span id= >Naddur</span></a><br><span id=notbold>15 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This item is one of the best items in the game for clerics, wizards, druids, and magicians.<br><br>In the endgame only one thing is greater then +mana to the above classes, and that is FT.&nbsp;&nbsp;FT is key for clerics and wizards, druids usually get shafted and magicians need a giant mana base for their Mod Roding.<br><br>As a 60 Cleric that has killed some of the biggest mobs in the game I can attest that necros and hybrids would shun this item.  Necros need large HP base so they can lich down and pump clerics and wizards.<br><br>Try doing the burrower beast in the deep sometime, I have used all my mana, and had to mod about 8 times in one fight (I was a CH rotation cleric).  So an extra 125mana would be huge.  negative 50 hps is nothing, if i were to pull agro from AoW or the Burrower Beast I would be losing 2,000 hps per attack round.  This means I die in approximatly 2 rounds, 50 hps isnt gonna do a thing to help me.<br><br>Endgame mobs should NEVER hit your casters, no if and or buts about it.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
